ain: ~3 hours\n- Linguistic attraction: City of Arts and Sciences + Valencian paella cooking class with local instructors\n\nDay 13: Valencia, Spain (Valencian)\n- Linguistic attraction: Turia Gardens walking tour + local market interactions in Valencian\n\nDay 14: Valencia to Madrid, Spain (Spanish)\n- Train: ~2 hours\n- Linguistic attraction: Cervantes Institute + return flight from Madrid\n\n**TRAIN ROUTES SUMMARY:**\n- Denver to Lisbon: Flight (unavoidable international travel)\n- Lisbon → Porto: 3 hours\n- Porto → Santiago: 2.5 hours\n- Santiago → Bilbao: 5 hours\n- Bilbao → Toulouse: 7 hours\n- Toulouse → Barcelona: 4.5 hours\n- Barcelona → Valencia: 3 hours\n- Valencia → Madrid: 2 hours\n- Madrid to Denver: Flight (return)\n\nPlease validate weather for each city and calculate train costs and total budget feasibility.", "recipient_id": 2}, {"action": "message", "content": "I've provided Agent 2 with the preliminary itinerary. Please check weather forecasts for each of these cities for the specific dates (starting tomorrow through 14 days). The cities are: Lisbon, Porto, Santiago de Compostela, Bilbao, Toulouse, Barcelona, Valencia, and Madrid. Flag any locations with expected rain so we can adjust the itinerary. Also validate train route feasibility.", "recipient_id": 1}]}
